author: @ayu_gyu
text:
"The world looks so beautiful from the outside & it seems to run well but if you look inside, everyone's trying so hard to get through it (Fvck but fight for my life)" - Woozi 2023

After recent events when we lost someone precious to us, we can see the dark side of K-Pop, everything looks bright & happy from the outside but from the inside there's so much struggle from constant practice, extreme diet, no dating, maintaining a perfect image & face, being hated by antis, treated unfairly, so many restrictions that one can lose sight of what they had wanted before & questioning whether it was worth it, the things they love the most is now a job. This is not just applicable to them but to every one of us. I hope this message in the song reaches a lot of people & they can think positively.

author: @dianamontoya4413
text:
Watching this interview was very interesting. Apparently both boys already knew each other quite well, but for reasons of their respective agencies, they had not been able to meet in public. Finally, agency stuff. On the other hand, and being honest, we needed to talk more about Woozi and less about Suga. I think if a person hosts a talk show, they should listen to the person they are hosting and talk less about themselves. I guess that's the writer's fault more than Suga's, but if it seemed to me then, they should have made a second part.
There were too many things to mention, things that would explain the reason for several decisions by Woozi and Pledis. Among them is the fact that this boy is fluent in several instruments, sang in a choir as a child, and can also read music. And that's just a bit of what he failed to mention, mostly because there wasn't an opportunity to do so, and also, Woozi is a very modest man.
I hope they do a second part, because it's really worth getting to know Woozi more deeply, and if Suga does the interview, I guess it will give us the pleasure of seeing them together again.

author: @madamec1990
text:
Dear Woozi.

Aku sudah mengikuti Seventeen sejak era 'Mansae'. Alasan aku jadi "Carat" karena aku merasa semua lagu yang dirilis Seventeen itu seolah-olah diciptakan khusus untukku, dan aku juga sangat suka tarian dan penampilan Seventeen saat di atas panggung. Aku bukan penggemar awalnya, tapi aku suka semua lagu yang dirilis oleh Seventeen. Aku menunggu kalian 'comeback" dengan sangat excited, perasaan itu masih aku rasakan sampai sekarang. Perasaan bersemangat dan penuh harapan setiap kali kalian 'Comeback" tidak pernah berubah sejak tahun 2016. Aku pernah khawatir 'apakah aku akan tetap menyukai lagu-lagu seventeen jika Seventeen berganti genre/tema?' tapi anehnya, jenis lagu apapun yang kalian rilis .. aku masih merasa lagu itu diciptakan khusus untukku. Semua lagu itu seakan-akan diletakan di dalam kotak kado, dan ketika aku membukanya ... tadaa! itu adalah hadiah yang sangat aku sukai, seakan-akan sang pengirim tahu bahwa hadiah ini adalah hadiah yang telah lama aku nantikan.

 
Teruntuk Woozi dan semua member Seventeen yang sudah bekerja keras selama ini, terima kasih banyak untuk semua karya yang telah kalian berikan. Kami (Carat) selalu menjadi orang-orang yang mendukung kalian, jadi kalian tidak perlu khawatir dan hanya perlu menikmati pekerjaan kalian.

Seperti bagian perasaan bahagia yang diberikan Seventeen untukku yang tidak pernah berubah sejak awal, aku harap Seventeen juga tidak kehilangan perasaan senang, antusias, dan berdebar penuh antisipasi saat tampil di atas panggung. Aku harap kalian bisa selalu menikmati pekerjaan kalian sebagaimana aku menikmati hasil karya yang telah kalian berikan.

Seventeen, fighting!

I absolutely love how much Seventeen just. Love each other? You can clearly tell both SVT and BTS have this in commonâ€” the group is always the number one priority. Period. text: Seventeen was supposed to debut with 17 members but the line up never happened. So instead seventeen stands for 13 members+ 3 units(vocal, hiphop & performance)+ 1 team.

author: @hikariai917
text:
Pledis intended to go with 17members,however as time passed, 13 members were ready to debut. Thus, these 13 members came out with the definition of a 3-team unit that is Hiphop unit,Performance unit, and Vocal unit. Still, they are 1 team all together. 

17 also signify their journey from trainee, their youth. That is how Seventeen (17) is a group with thirteen members

text:
What I like about this is when Woozi said that he makes music that the members like, and in turn it is music that CARATS like.

It aligns with my principle that you make music for yourself, and that sincerity and genuineness will reflect with the listeners and fans you gain.

I think that's one of the perks of being an idol producer, having some control on the color of the music you bring into the group.

text: It also reflects how the fans like their idols for a reason. How not only the song turns out great but it also just matches the fans' taste. text: @SimplySimran Dude, I know all the compositing programs! Do you even realize what a "Garage Band" is?! It's so unprofessional and it's for kids who want to have fun. Without basic knowledge of solfege and harmony, you cannot compose at a high level! In general, what he explains is funny! text:
â€‹@Ekaterina Georgieva  The garage band that he used was the first composing program that he know for the first time in his life when he was 15yo. He was self taught composing with garage band during his trainee by accident. And his Vical trainer which also music producer see his potential and began to teach him about composing ofc not with garage band.
I think you need to finish watching the full interview first.

Just some additional information about woozi that not discussed on this interview so you can know Woozi's music background before he join Pledis at 15yo

He first put interest in music after learning to play instruments such as piano, guitar, drums and clarinet in an English academy he used to attend when he was a kid.

Woozi competed in many classical music competitions when he was in elementary school until he was in the second grade of middle school.

He originally wanted to pursue a career as a classical musician.

With little expectation, he applied for Pledis Entertainment open audition. With a competition rate of 300:1, Woozi passed the audition and joined the agency in April 2011.

author: @KatieGeorgieva
text: @SimplySimran Dude, why are you arguing with me when you're a non professional? I graduated from the Central Music School in Moscow! Which is this school you can check yourself on Google. I was the first to be admitted to the Tchaikovsky Conservatory, which has rooms with the names of great composers and performers who studied there. You can check for yourself who they are. You can check for yourself who the professors are at this educational institution at the moment. And that's why I tell you that this boy tells stories for little children! If you're so stubborn, I can ask one of the professors of solfege or composition to write a short summary here so that you realize how ridiculous what he claims is!

author: @KatieGeorgieva
text: @@whoami8744 Dude, 15 is way too late to start composing! This is only possible if he has been a professional pianist for many years. Moreover, in order to use "Garage Band" without a piano, he must be an absolutist (a person with a perfect pitch). It also takes years to train an absolute (even though you are born one). That is why in music schools there are separate solfege groups for pianists and violinists (who must be absolute masters) and other instruments. Composition is taught in a separate group for theorists, and there solfeggio is twice as complex as that of absolutists, which, believe me, is incredibly complex. Do you want me to show you the program of the composition department at the Conservatory so that you realize how complex the theory of this discipline is? This boy claims to create complex songs. He does not compose children songs. For this reason, it is IMPOSSIBLE that they were created by a guy who two years ago learned to compose with "Garage Band"!

author: @KatieGeorgieva
text: @SimplySimran Dude, he claims he started at age 15 with no knowledge of solfege! Read my other comment to the other person I replied to. The theory of composers is very complex and is learned in early years. Again: if you want, I will download here the program of the composition department at the Tchaikovsky Conservatory so that you can see for yourself how complicated the theory is and how much is required to know how to compose at a high level. Seventeen's songs are complex enough to require at least a basic theoretical knowledge. Are you saying the songs are mediocre? Because with non-professional knowledge of composition, only children's songs can be created!

Well, it warms my heart because you see the excitement in the guest's eyes.

I love seeing people chasing their dreams and making them true.
I want to wish Woozi, Seventeen, BTS, .and Suga the very best of luck in all they do.
I love you all
